<promed@promedmail.org>
[The text of the 2nd report is ambiguous. But, if it is correct that
the receptor binding site of the hemagglutinin of some avian
influenza A (H5N1) viruses has undergone change, then this is a very
significant development, because it is this region of the
hemagglutinin molecule that can determine tissue-specific binding
properties and ultimately the host range of the virus. - Mod.CP]
